---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Between-Session Support | Rabbia Psychologist"
  description="Continue support after therapy, assessments, or school meetings with structured parent guidance, home routines, behaviour support, and practical between-session plans."
>
  <div class="bg-brand-cream py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">Support That Continues Between Sessions</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Parents often leave therapy, school meetings, or assessments with advice but struggle to apply it at home. Rabbia Psychologist Child Development Services provides structured between-session support programs so families can continue progress with clearer routines, practical tools, and guided next steps.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl space-y-12">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Why between-session support matters</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Consistency at home is critical. These programs empower parents to actively support their child's development in everyday situations.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Who this is for</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Families looking to bridge the gap between formal sessions, seeking structured home strategies, or needing targeted advice following an assessment.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">What the program may include</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Customized resource packets, strategy checklists, behavior logs, and step-by-step parent guides tailored to your child's needs.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Parent home plans</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Structured outlines for maintaining daily routines and practicing developmental goals.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Behaviour and routine support</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Actionable advice for navigating transitions, managing outbursts, and establishing calm, predictable environments.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">School carryover support</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Tools to help implement IEP recommendations and classroom strategies at home.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">ASD/ADHD support planning</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Specialized guidance designed to support executive function, sensory needs, and emotional regulation.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Report-to-action planning</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Breaking down professional evaluations into practical, everyday steps.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">Program Examples</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
          <li>2-week Parent Support Plan</li>
          <li>4-week Home Routine Support Plan</li>
          <li>School Meeting Preparation Plan</li>
          <li>ASD Parent Starter Plan</li>
          <li>ADHD Routine and Executive Function Plan</li>
          <li>Behaviour Tracking and Response Plan</li>
          <li>Report Review to Action Plan</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">Service Boundaries</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
          These programs are designed to support parent understanding, home carryover, and practical implementation. They do not replace emergency care, local medical services, school services, diagnosis, or regulated therapy where those are required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/book" class="inline-block px-8 py-4 bg-brand-navy text-white rounded-lg font-bold text-lg hover:bg-blue-900 transition-all shadow-lg">
          Book Consultation
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
